                <h1>What is Legionnaires Disease?</h1>
                <hr>
                <p>
                    Legionnaires Disease (also known as Legionella) is a severe form of lung infection which is spread by water sources and articial water supply systems such as air conditioning systems. Often mis-diagnosed as flu or pneumonia, the disease is most likely to affect men over the age of 45 with deficient immune systems, are smokers or have exisiting breathing problems.
                </p>
                <br>
                <p>
                    In some cases the infection can become so severe that it can be life-threathening and between 2011 and 2013 the NHS recorded 84 deaths as a direct result of Legionella.
                </p>
                <br>
                <p>
                    <strong>If you are the owner of a domestic property which is used for rental accomodation it is your responsibility to undertake a Legionella inspection in order to protect your tenants.</strong>
                </p>
                <br>
